  "text": "The pedestrians in this work are deemed to be healthy adults for the purposes of assigning pedestrian properties. Adult pedestrian weight is represented by a log-normal distribution with a mean of 73.85 kg and a standard deviation of 15.68 kg [CITATION_1] . The stride length is taken here to be normally distributed with a mean of 0.66 m [CITATION_2] , and assuming a coefficient of variation of 10%, a standard deviation of 0.066 m is used. As reported in Table 1 , the pacing frequency is considered as normally distributed with a mean of 1.96 Hz and standard deviation of 0.209 Hz. The phase angle, φ, of a pedestrian's vertical harmonic force is taken to be uniformly random in the interval 0 to 2π.",
